<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9295] Remove Unicode BOM (U+FEFF) from text files in codebase</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9295</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When starting Solr built from the master branch on Windows, this is what you see:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;C:\Users\elyograg\git\lucene-solr\solr&amp;gt;bin\solr start

C:\Users\elyograg\git\lucene-solr\solr&amp;gt;&#8745;&#9559;&#9488;@REM
&apos;&#8745;&#9559;&#9488;@REM&apos; is not recognized as an internal or external command,
operable program or batch file.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The three extra characters, found at the very beginning of the solr.cmd script, are a Unicode BOM, and are invisible to vim, notepad, and notepad++.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem does not exist in 6.1.0, but IS present in branch_6x and master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using grep to find this character in the entire codebase, I found one other relevant file with a BOM.  All others were binary (images, jars, git pack files, etc):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;./solr/webapp/web/js/lib/jquery.blockUI.js&lt;/p&gt;</description>
