                            <comment id="15371549" author="erickerickson" created="Mon, 11 Jul 2016 20:30:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for catching this!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15371985" author="steve_rowe" created="Tue, 12 Jul 2016 00:42:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The following pattern added to the &lt;tt&gt;invalidPatterns&lt;/tt&gt; array in the &lt;tt&gt;source-patterns&lt;/tt&gt; groovy script included with the top-level ant target &lt;tt&gt;-validate-source-patterns&lt;/tt&gt; successfully found the two files &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=elyograg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;elyograg&quot;&gt;elyograg&lt;/a&gt; found (after I checked out the commit just before his):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;(~$/^\uFEFF/$) : &apos;UTF-8 byte order mark&apos;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;-validate-source-patterns:
[source-patterns] UTF-8 byte order mark: solr/bin/solr.cmd
[source-patterns] UTF-8 byte order mark: solr/webapp/web/js/lib/jquery.blockUI.js

BUILD FAILED
/Users/sarowe/git/lucene-solr-3/build.xml:132: Found 2 violations in source files (UTF-8 byte order mark).
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tested that it only flags beginning-of-file occurrences by prepending junk to &lt;tt&gt;solr/bin/solr.cmd&lt;/tt&gt; - &lt;tt&gt;od -c&lt;/tt&gt; shows the BOM was still present, just not at the beginning - and &lt;tt&gt;-validate-source-patterns&lt;/tt&gt; didn&apos;t complain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committing shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
